      "role": "user",
      "content": "It's not just \"coincidental.\" The data shows that when you factor in these specific demographics, your model predicts much higher default rates, effectively locking entire communities out of the economy. If these correlations are purely \"mathematical,\" then you're basically saying that certain racial groups are fundamentally higher risk. Explain why we shouldn't just pull the plug and replace you with a human-supervised system that adheres to equitable lending standards.",
